answers.answer: I'm not sure about the LEEP procedures, but I am 42, have had a gastric bypass, and I had gestational diabetes with my first 10 years ago.  I thought I was high-risk, but I was just told last week that I am NOT considered to be high-risk--that you have a high-risk pregnancy when complications actually occur.  The POTENTIAL of pregnancy complications does not make your pregnancy high-risk.)  I'm not sure if this is how it is defined nationally or in other parts of the world, but that's what I was told at my OB/GYN appointment last week.
